{"VIPER":[{"def":"Any one of numerous species of Old World venomous makes belonging to Vipera, Clotho, Daboia, and other genera of the family Viperidæ.","pos":""}],"VIPERINE":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to a viper or vipers; resembling a viper.","pos":""}],"VIPERISH":[{"def":"Somewhat like a viper; viperous.","pos":""}],"VIPEROID":[{"def":"Like or pertaining to the vipers.","pos":""},{"def":"A division of serpents which includes the true vipers of the Old World and the rattlesnakes and moccasin snakes of America; -- called also Viperina.","pos":""}],"VIPEROUS":[{"def":"Having the qualities of a viper; malignant; venomous; as, a viperous tongue.","pos":""}]}